com.github.dm.jrt.android.v11.stream

Interface LoaderStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the input data type.
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Channel<IN,OUT>, InvocationConfigurable<RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>>, Iterable<OUT>, Iterator<OUT>, Routine<IN,OUT>, RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>, com.github.dm.jrt.stream.builder.StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>

    public interface LoaderStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
extends com.github.dm.jrt.stream.builder.StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
    Interface defining a builder of routines concatenating map and reduce functions.
    Each function in the stream will be backed by a routine instance, which may have its own specific configuration and invocation mode.
    In order to prevent undesired leaks, the class of the specified functions must have a static scope.

    Note that, if at least one reduce function is part of the chain, the results will be propagated only when the built routine invocation completes.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 07/03/2016.

        @NotNull
<AFTER> LoaderStreamBuilder<IN,AFTER> map(@NotNull
                                                   ContextInvocationFactory<? super OUT,? extends AFTER> factory)
        Concatenates a stream based on the specified mapping invocation factory to this one.

        Note that the created routine will be initialized with the current configuration.
        Note also that this stream will be bound as a result of the call.

        Type Parameters:
        AFTER - the concatenation output type.
        Parameters:
        factory - the context invocation factory.
        Returns:
        the new stream instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the loader context is not set.

      • on

        @NotNull
LoaderStreamBuilder<IN,OUT> on(@Nullable
                                        LoaderContext context)
        Sets the stream loader context.
        The context will be used by all the concatenated routines until changed.
        If null it will cause the next routines to employ the configured runner instead of an Android loader.
        Parameters:
        context - the loader context.
        Returns:
        the new stream instance.

      • streamLoaderConfiguration

        @NotNull
LoaderConfiguration.Builder<? extends LoaderStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>> streamLoaderConfiguration()
        Gets the loader configuration builder related to the whole stream.
        The configuration options will be applied to all the next concatenated routines unless overwritten by specific ones.

        Note that the configuration builder will be initialized with the current stream configuration.

        Returns:
        the invocation configuration builder.
